    "goal_understanding": "The goal of the game is to navigate a grid-based puzzle and activate all goal cells in each level by matching the carried piece's shape, color, and rotation to the goal's requirements simultaneously. The player must manage stamina, avoid walls, and strategically step on modifier tiles to alter the piece's attributes before reaching the goals. Completing all goals advances to the next level, and the ultimate objective is to win all levels without running out of lives.",
    "mechanics_understanding": "The player controls a piece that has three attributes: shape (0\u20135), color (orange, blue, green, red), and rotation (0\u00b0, 90\u00b0, 180\u00b0, 270\u00b0). Each move costs 1 stamina. If stamina reaches 0, a life is lost and stamina resets to its maximum. Losing all lives ends the game in GAME_OVER. The grid contains walls (impassable), floor (walkable), and special tiles: shape modifiers (cycle shape), color modifiers (cycle color in order orange\u2192blue\u2192green\u2192red\u2192orange), rotation modifiers (rotate 90\u00b0 clockwise). Goal cells require specific combinations of shape, color, and rotation; stepping on a goal with matching attributes completes it. All goals in a level must be completed to progress. Blocked directions indicate walls, and moves into them are wasted turns, so they must be avoided."
  },
